      Methods in fast3d with parameters of type Graphics3d 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void Renderable.render(Graphics3d g)
      called when this renderables is requested to draw itself on screen on the way prior calculated by shade()
      void Panel3d.render(Graphics3d g)
      called on every paintComponent-call
      draws the universe
      subclasses are requested to call super, because of the automatically render of the universe
      void Renderable.shade(Graphics3d s)
      called when this renderable is requested to calculate where to draw on screen
      the graphics-context is not clipped, so it is greatly needed to really just draw itself
      during this method is is highly recommended to not draw anything

      Modifier and Type Method and Description

      renders all objects in the sorted, correct order
      void Object.render(Graphics3d g)
      calls render() for every hold Group, but in the sorted, right order
      void Group.render(Graphics3d g)
      a group renders all of its triangles in the correct order
      if some groups may intersect each other user-recognizable, every triangle of those groups should be rendered directly by adding them to the universe using addToUniverse()

      called when the parameter should be rendered

      void Scene.shade(Graphics3d g)

      void Object.shade(Graphics3d g)

    • Uses of Graphics3d in fast3d.graphics

      Subclasses of Graphics3d in fast3d.graphics 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  Turtle3d
      gives the ability to draw directly into a 3d-scenery like a turtle
      each turtle-method starts with t
      you can move around in the scenery drawing lines or not (specified by tsetPen(Color or null)), push and pop on a history of transformations and rotate the turtle on it's own coordinate system
      on default the pen is down
